<m0>NOMO: RARE ROAD VICTORY<ql>
<m1><styl>vs,2<ql>
<styl>txt<ql>
<ep>
<m0>   PITTSBURGH (--) Hideo Nomo won for the first time in three road starts this season and Raul Mondesi hit one of three Los Angeles homers as the Dodgers defeated Pittsburgh.<ep>
   Mike Piazza, hitless in two games since ending a 16-game hitting streak, added a two-run homer off John Hope (1-2). Greg Gagne added a three-run shot in the ninth off Joe Boever as homers accounted for all eight Dodgers' runs.<ep>
   The homers awakened a Dodgers' offense whose 121 runs scored before Monday were the second-fewest in the majors ahead of Florida.<ep>
   Nomo (5-2) wasn't nearly as dominating as he was in striking out 30 Pirates in two starts last season. He allowed four runs and eight hits in seven-plus innings, striking out five. He left after Mark Johnson's two-run homer in the eighth made it 5-4.<ql>
