<m0>   PHILADELPHIA (--) James Mouton had a two-run homer and a two-run double and Doug Drabek allowed three hits over seven innings as Houston beat Philadelphia.<ep>
   Drabek (1-2) struck out nine and walked four. He allowed one earned run, Todd Zeile's fourth homer of the season in the fourth inning. The Phillies' other run against him came in the seventh on an error by first baseman Jeff Bagwell.<ql>
